==Latin==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[amare]]'', '''love''' + ''-ic'' adjective ending, used as [[substantive]]

===Noun===
'''amicus''', '''[[Wiktionary Appendix:Latin second declension|-i]]''' ''m''

Feminine is ''[[amica]]''.

Antonym: [[inimicus]].

